                  <dt>Provenance</dt>
          <dd>Gaston-Alexandre Camentron, Paris, France, sold; [to Durand-Ruel (1896-1906) sold]; to Adrien Hébrard, Paris, (1906), sold; [to Durand-Ruel, Paris, October 24, 1906- August 5, 1912) sold]; [to Galerie Thannhauser, 1912 - ?]. Oscar Schmitz, Dresden, ( by 1920 -1933); by descent to his son Edward A. Schmitz, Dresden (1933-1936?) sold; [through Wildenstein & Company, New York, NY, 1937, sold]; to Grenville Lindall Winthrop (1937 - 1943), New York, NY, bequest; to Fogg Art Museum, 1943. <br />
<br />
Notes:<br />
Published by Scheffler 1920 as in Schmitz collection.  When he left Germany in 1931, Oscar Schmitz took his collection to Switzerland.  After his death, his son made arrangements to sell the collection.</dd>
        
        
        
